.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/styles-library-utilization/retrieval-engine.md:3:description: "Default flat-file retrieval behind the legacy|shadow|persistent adapter, with deterministic eligibility-first ranking and guarded hydration."
.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/styles-library-utilization/retrieval-engine.md:18:The styles library has a committed flat-file retrieval engine over 1,290 bundles. The `legacy|shadow|persistent` adapter defaults to this legacy path, so the flat files remain authoritative. The engine returns bounded candidate cards and hydrates a selected record only when the checked manifest, live corpus and request generation still agree.
.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/styles-library-utilization/retrieval-engine.md:26:`style-library.mjs` exposes manifest build or check, query and hydrate commands through the adapter. In its default `legacy` mode, query applies required facets, exclusions, provenance and rights eligibility before lexical ordering. The disposable in-memory full-text projection speeds ordering when available, while a bounded source scan preserves the same eligible set when the accelerator is unavailable.
