.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/feature-catalog/manual-scan-verify-status/code-graph-status.md:25:When tombstone auditing is enabled with `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_TOMBSTONES=true`, status includes retained deletion lineage from the graph stats summary: counts by kind and reason plus recent retained tombstones. With the flag unset, the audit remains default-off and live graph queries continue to read only active nodes and edges. The retained set is bounded by `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_TOMBSTONE_LIMIT`, default 100: every tombstone-recording write prunes the table to the most recent rows by deletion time, so a flat retention of 100 entries survives unless the operator raises the cap. The limit is clamped to a maximum of 10000, and a non-positive or unparseable value falls back to the default of 100.
