.opencode/skills/sk-git/feature-catalog/worktree-naming/pre-push-naming-enforcement.md:30:Git feeds the hook one line per pushed ref on stdin: local ref, local sha, remote ref, remote sha. The hook only inspects `refs/heads/*` lines — tags and other ref kinds pass through untouched — and the naming gate only checks a ref whose remote sha is all-zeros, meaning the push would create a new remote branch. A push that only updates a branch already present on the remote is always naming-exempt (migration tolerance): a legacy branch pushed before this grammar existed is never retroactively rejected on name alone. `skilled/v*` release branches are exempt from BOTH gates entirely, new or existing.
.opencode/skills/sk-git/feature-catalog/worktree-naming/pre-push-naming-enforcement.md:67:- Canonical catalog source: `feature-catalog.md`
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/javascript/quality-standards/overview-modules-and-docs.md:43:| `.js/.cjs` Node utilities outside plugin loader paths | CommonJS with `'use strict'` | Default for legacy runtime helpers and standalone scripts |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/javascript/quality-standards/overview-modules-and-docs.md:64:pattern applies to legacy `.js/.cjs` utility surfaces and test runners that use
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/governance/feature-flag-governance.md:35:Live runtime governance does exist. `isFeatureEnabled()` implements default-on, explicit-opt-out semantics: a flag stays enabled unless it is explicitly set to `false` or `0`. Global rollout percentage is read from `SPECKIT_ROLLOUT_PERCENT`, and partial rollout is fail-closed when no identity is provided, so a missing identity does not silently bypass gating.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/governance/feature-flag-governance.md:39:Memory roadmap defaults are also governed in code. Missing or invalid roadmap phase values resolve to `scope-governance`, while dormant roadmap flags remain intentionally default-off where required. In particular, adaptive ranking stays off unless explicitly enabled, even though most graduated roadmap flags inherit the default-on rollout helper.
