.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/mutation/correction-tracking-with-undo.md:40:3. **Scoped causal edge deletion** -- removes only the causal edge that belongs to this specific correction. The primary path matches on the `Correction#{id}:` evidence prefix (where `{id}` is the correction row ID), so only the correction-owned edge is removed rather than every edge between the pair. If the edge still uses the older legacy evidence format without this prefix, the code falls back to a scoped legacy delete rather than removing every same-relation edge between the pair.
