.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/pipeline-architecture/daemon-ownership-reelection.md:3:description: "A default-on path that lets the shared mk-spec-memory daemon outlive its owner. The owner spawns the daemon detached and on shutdown releases it for a live secondary to keep instead of killing it. A fresh session that finds the released daemon under a stale lease reaps it before respawn, so the database keeps a single writer."
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/pipeline-architecture/daemon-ownership-reelection.md:19:This feature is default-on in the launcher code. It lets the shared mk-spec-memory daemon outlive the owner that spawned it, rather than dying when that owner's session ends, so concurrent sessions keep their MCP transport.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/pipeline-architecture/daemon-ownership-reelection.md:25:### Flag gate, default on
