.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/retrieval/semantic-and-lexical-search-memorysearch.md:41:When trace is enabled, result envelopes now expose bounded graph diagnostics without altering the non-trace contract: `trace.graphContribution` includes `raw`, `normalized`, `appliedBonus`, and `capApplied`. Any legacy `rolloutState` label is compatibility metadata only and is no longer part of the active operator contract, and requests forwarded from `memory_context` can also include `trace.sessionTransition`. Extended telemetry summarizes the same behavior through `transitionDiagnostics` and `graphWalkDiagnostics`.
