.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:198:The engine under the hood. `hybrid-search.ts` orchestrates multi-channel retrieval with five search channels, adaptive fusion, diversity reranking and a multi-tier fallback chain. This pipeline provides the candidate generation and fusion components used by Stage 1 of the 4-stage pipeline; the legacy V1 path is no longer present in runtime routing.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:208:The fallback chain (`searchWithFallback()`) provides resilience. When `SPECKIT_SEARCH_FALLBACK` is enabled, the default path is a three-tier degradation flow: Tier 1 primary retrieval (default minimum similarity 0.3), Tier 2 widened retrieval at 0.1 inside the caller-allowed channel set, and Tier 3 structural SQL search as last resort for still-allowed lexical channels. Tier 3 now excludes archived rows unless `includeArchived=true`, closing the fallback-only leak that could reintroduce archived memories after earlier stages had filtered them. When `SPECKIT_SEARCH_FALLBACK` is disabled, the legacy two-pass path is used (0.3 then 0.17). The system is designed to avoid empty returns except on hard failures.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:212:See [`retrieval/hybrid-search-pipeline.md`](../feature-catalog/retrieval/hybrid-search-pipeline.md) for full implementation and test file listings.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:234:The pipeline is the sole runtime path. The legacy `postSearchPipeline` is no longer present in runtime routing, and `SPECKIT_PIPELINE_V2` is no longer consumed by runtime code.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:238:See [`retrieval/4-stage-pipeline-architecture.md`](../feature-catalog/retrieval/4-stage-pipeline-architecture.md) for full implementation and test file listings.
