.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:1067:Feedback learning now has three reducer surfaces: a read-only shared aggregator, a default-off deferred session-trace causal reducer, and a feedback-aware retention reducer that requires shadow-first safety evidence before active changes. The reducers share aggregate fields while preserving independent default-off behavior.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:1075:See [`analysis/learning-feedback-reducers.md`](../feature-catalog/analysis/learning-feedback-reducers.md) for full implementation and test file listings.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:1097:See [`evaluation/ablation-studies-evalrunablation.md`](../feature-catalog/evaluation/ablation-studies-evalrunablation.md) for full implementation and test file listings.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:1113:This is a read-only module. It queries the eval database and produces reports with no writes or mutation side effects. The accessor now tries `getEvalDb()` before falling back to `initEvalDb()`, so it keeps using an already-selected non-default or test eval DB instead of silently switching back to the default one. Two different limits apply: the request `limit` keeps only the most recent sprint groups after grouping, while `SPECKIT_DASHBOARD_LIMIT` caps dashboard SQL reads. Snapshot rows are still fetched directly, but channel data is grouped per included eval-run/channel pair before sprint aggregation so large per-query histories do not starve the kept sprint groups.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:1117:See [`evaluation/reporting-dashboard-evalreportingdashboard.md`](../feature-catalog/evaluation/reporting-dashboard-evalreportingdashboard.md) for full implementation and test file listings.
