.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/scoring-and-calibration/retrieval-rescue-authority.md:21:The rescue layer is default-on unless `SPECKIT_RERANK_LAYER=false`. It computes lexical rescue signals from query-token coverage, trigger phrase coverage, document-type hints, title/path hits, quality penalties, and archive penalties. It can hydrate richer candidate rows, backfill weak lexical coverage, inject sibling documents inside the caller's scope/folder boundary, and then sort by the effective score after rescue metadata is attached.
