   450	| `SPECKIT_RETENTION_SWEEP` | `true` | boolean | Governed memory retention sweep. Graduated ON. Set `false` to disable the background interval. Manual `memory_retention_sweep` remains available. | `lib/session/session-manager.ts` |
   451	| `SPECKIT_RETENTION_SWEEP_INTERVAL_MS` | `3600000` | number | Background retention sweep interval in milliseconds. Values must be positive integers. Invalid values fall back to one hour. | `lib/session/session-manager.ts` |
   452	| `SPECKIT_IDEMPOTENCY_RECEIPT_TTL_DAYS` | `30` | number (positive int) | Retention window, in days, for stored idempotency-replay receipts before pruning. An explicit caller argument takes precedence. Invalid/non-positive values fall back to the default (minimum 1). | `lib/storage/idempotency-receipts.ts` |
   453	| `SPECKIT_MEMORY_IDEMPOTENCY` | `false` | boolean (opt-in `1`/`true`/`yes`/`on`) | Default-off server-derived replay receipts for `memory_save`/`memory_update`, plus advisory `near_duplicate_of` hints. Default OFF, so set an enabled value to opt in. | `lib/storage/idempotency-receipts.ts` |
   454	| `SPECKIT_SOFT_DELETE_TOMBSTONES` | `false` | boolean (`'true'`) | Default-off tombstone delete path for memory deletes and the purgeable retention partition. Keep OFF until recall surfaces filter `deleted_at IS NULL`, then set `true` to enable. | `handlers/memory-crud-delete.ts`, `lib/governance/memory-retention-sweep.ts` |
   455	| `SESSION_TTL_MINUTES` | `30` | number | Working-memory session TTL in minutes. | `lib/session/session-manager.ts` |
   456	| `SESSION_MAX_ENTRIES` | `100` | number | Maximum working-memory entries retained per session. | `lib/session/session-manager.ts` |
   457	| `DISABLE_SESSION_DEDUP` | `false` | boolean | Disables session-level deduplication when set to lowercase `true`. | `lib/session/session-manager.ts` |
   458	| `SESSION_DEDUP_DB_UNAVAILABLE_MODE` | `block` | enum: `block`, `allow` | Chooses whether session dedup blocks or allows operation when its database path is unavailable. | `lib/session/session-manager.ts` |
   459	| `STALE_CLEANUP_INTERVAL_MS` | `3600000` | number | Interval for background stale-session cleanup. | `lib/session/session-manager.ts` |
   460	| `STALE_SESSION_THRESHOLD_MS` | `86400000` | number | Inactivity threshold before a session is considered stale. | `lib/session/session-manager.ts` |
   461	| `SPECKIT_MEMORY_SESSION_ID` | (unset) | string | Explicit override for the no-session `memory_context` anchor. When set, the trimmed value is used as the session-bucket anchor instead of the scope-derived or single-user default. It is not a governance boundary. | `handlers/memory-context.ts` |
   462	| `SPECKIT_AC_COVERAGE` | `false` | boolean | Opt-in acceptance-criteria coverage scan during spec validation. When unset, the registered rule exits pass with no warnings, preserving strict-validation results for existing folders. | `scripts/rules/check-ac-coverage.sh` |
   463	| `SPECKIT_AC_COVERAGE_FLOOR` | `0.9` | number | Minimum covered acceptance-criteria ratio for the advisory scan. Values outside `[0,1]` are clamped before the floor is calculated. | `scripts/rules/check-ac-coverage.sh` |
   464	| `SPECKIT_AUTHORED_CONTINUITY_SNAPSHOT` | `false` | flag (`"1"`) | Opt-in compact-hook authored continuity snapshot mode. When set, the hook can emit the authored snapshot path instead of relying only on transcript-derived fallback context. | `mcp-server/hooks/claude/compact-inject.ts` |
   465	| `SPECKIT_COMPLETION_FRESHNESS` | `false` | boolean | Enables the strict-only completion freshness validation rule. The rule recomputes the packet content fingerprint and compares it with stored continuity metadata. Unset preserves existing validation output. | `scripts/validation/continuity-freshness.ts`, `mcp-server/tests/continuity-freshness.vitest.ts` |
   466	| `SPECKIT_COMPLETION_FRESHNESS_ENFORCE` | `false` | boolean | When completion freshness is enabled, promotes stale freshness findings from warning to error. | `scripts/validation/continuity-freshness.ts`, `mcp-server/tests/continuity-freshness.vitest.ts` |
   467	| `SPECKIT_IDENTITY_MERGE_SAFETY` | `true` | boolean | Shared spec-folder identity resolver and lineage-merge guard. **Default ON** (graduated). Both generators resolve a specs-root-relative identity and the merge preserves a non-null parent and unions children, so a scoped or null-deriving re-derive can no longer erase lineage. Set `false`/`0`/`off` to restore the legacy caller-base path and spread merge. | `lib/config/capability-flags.ts` |
   468	| `SPECKIT_GENERATED_METADATA_GRANDFATHER` | `false` | boolean | Grandfather report mode for the `GENERATED_METADATA_INTEGRITY` rule. **Default OFF, enforcing** (graduated): a violation is a hard strict error. Set `true`/`1` to restore the non-blocking report mode for a tree that has not been restamped. | `lib/config/capability-flags.ts` |
   469	| `SPECKIT_STATUS_COMPLETION_CONSISTENCY_GATE` | `false` | boolean | Cross-checks a stored `derived.status: complete` against `completion_pct`/open `tasks.md` items, inside the `GENERATED_METADATA_INTEGRITY` rule. **Default OFF, report mode** (inverse polarity from the grandfather flag above): a disagreement surfaces in `--strict` output without failing the run, because a repo-wide sweep found 213 folders already mislabeled `complete` by a prior `deriveStatus` defect. Set `true`/`1` to enforce (fails strict) once the existing backlog is reviewed. | `lib/config/capability-flags.ts`, `lib/validation/generated-metadata-integrity.ts` |
   470	| `SPECKIT_METADATA_DISK_CONSISTENCY_ENFORCE` | `true` | boolean | Advisory→enforce toggle for the `METADATA_DISK_PATH_CONSISTENCY` rule. **Default ON, enforcing (graduated 2026-07-10)**: a `description.json`/`graph-metadata.json` path mismatch against the folder's actual on-disk path fails `--strict`. Graduated on a reconciled tree-wide census across ~2,420 spec folders (1,130 real mismatches — mostly a stale `system-spec-kit`→`system-speckit` directory-rename prefix plus a stale `continuity.packet_pointer` frontmatter field — found and reconciled via the canonical generators plus a targeted frontmatter fix; the remaining ~74-folder residual is entirely non-production paths: deliberately-synthetic test fixtures, a reserved not-yet-built `z-future/` namespace, timestamped `.backup-*` snapshots, and auxiliary research/scratch subdirectories never meant to be validated as standalone spec folders — see `019-validation-enforce-graduation/implementation-summary.md`). Set `false`/`0` to fall back to advisory-only. | `scripts/rules/check-metadata-disk-consistency.sh` |
   471	| `SPECKIT_STATUS_CROSS_DOC_ENFORCE` | `true` | boolean | Advisory→enforce toggle for the `STATUS_CROSS_DOC_CONSISTENCY` rule. **Default ON, enforcing (graduated 2026-07-10)**: a classified-status disagreement between `spec.md` and `implementation-summary.md` fails `--strict`. Graduated on a reconciled tree-wide census across ~2,420 spec folders (128 real mismatches found and reconciled to 2 honestly-documented residuals — see `019-validation-enforce-graduation/implementation-summary.md`). Set `false`/`0` to fall back to advisory-only. | `scripts/rules/check-status-cross-doc-consistency.sh`, `scripts/lib/status-classifier.sh` |
   472	| `SPECKIT_CHILD_DRIFT_ENFORCE` | `true` | boolean | Advisory→enforce toggle for the `GRAPH_METADATA_CHILD_DRIFT` rule. **Default ON, enforcing (graduated 2026-07-10)**: a phase parent's `graph-metadata.json.children_ids` missing an on-disk phase child the writer would add on its next refresh fails `--strict`. Unlike the other two flags in this graduation group, enforce mode also fails closed when the child-scanner dependency (`scripts/dist/spec/is-phase-parent.js`) is unavailable OR stale — gated by a dedicated `dist-freshness.cjs` entry (`system-spec-kit/scripts` package, `is-phase-parent` distEntry, scoped to just that one file's own dependency-free source rather than the package's whole-tree default, so unrelated concurrent edits elsewhere in `scripts/` never cause a false-stale result) built and fixture-tested before this flag graduated. Graduated on a reconciled tree-wide census across ~2,420 spec folders — see `019-validation-enforce-graduation/implementation-summary.md`. Set `false`/`0` to fall back to advisory-only. | `scripts/rules/check-graph-metadata-child-drift.sh`, `scripts/lib/dist-freshness.cjs`, `scripts/spec/is-phase-parent.ts` |
   473	| `SPECKIT_VALIDATE_SCRIPT` | (bundled `scripts/spec/validate.sh`) | string (path) | Overrides the `validate.sh` path the `strict-pass-freshness.ts` sweep tool invokes per folder when re-baselining strict-pass freshness across multiple spec roots. Unset resolves the committed script next to the sweep tool. | `scripts/sweep/strict-pass-freshness.ts` |
   474	| `SPECKIT_GENERATED_METADATA_DRIFT_GATE` | `true` | boolean | Synopsis drift gate and shared-extractor routing. **Default ON** (graduated): grandfather report mode keeps drift non-blocking, both fields keep their legacy extractors, and no `source_doc_hashes` persist (generated bytes unchanged). When set both `description` and `causal_summary` derive from the one shared synopsis extractor, `source_doc_hashes` persist as the freshness key, and a drift report fails strict validation. | `lib/config/capability-flags.ts` |
   475	| `SPECKIT_GENERATED_METADATA_Z_EXCLUSION` | `true` | boolean | Excludes `z_*` staging and archive folders from the global descriptions.json cache. **Default ON**: set `false` to restore the prior scanner that included them. | `lib/search/folder-discovery.ts` |
   476	| `SPECKIT_IDEMPOTENT_DESCRIPTION_WRITES` | `true` | boolean | Content-gated description.json and global-cache writes. **Default ON** (graduated). A per-folder save that changes only the volatile stamp is skipped, the aggregate cache write is gated on a real member delta, and the targeted upsert replaces only the changed entry. Set `false`/`0`/`off` to restore the unconditional legacy write. | `lib/config/capability-flags.ts` |
   477	| `SPECKIT_ENTITY_CONFIG_PATH` | (unset) | string (path) | Override path to a declarative entity-extraction rules JSON. When unset the built-in rules apply. A malformed or unreadable file falls back to the built-in rules. | `lib/extraction/entity-extractor.ts` |
