.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:3:description: "Planned-state record for the P0-to-P4 compiled-routing cutover. The ruling is settled (adopt the phased path); all runtime implementation remains future work gated on an operator go-ahead to begin P0."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:5:  - "compiled routing default-on planned summary"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:6:  - "P0 P4 cutover current status"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:11:    packet_pointer: "sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:47:| **Status** | Ruling settled (adopt the phased path P0->P4, decided on the analysis; reversible and operator-overridable). No runtime implementation started; a separate operator go-ahead gates P0. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:51:| **Repository default** | Unchanged; compiled routing remains default-off |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:60:The decision packet settles the ruling on the analysis: adopt a staged path to compiled routing as the effective default rather than flipping the default now. No runtime work has begun. The current live integration remains additive metadata only, the compiled and legacy decisions remain identical, and the repository flag remains off by default. The operator may override the ruling to flip-now at any time; that override is available but not blocking.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:76:Add re-mint-required CI for stale manifests, then enable compiled routing in one named environment profile while the repository default remains off.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:78:### P3 and P4: Eligibility and Effective Default
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:80:Derive both eligibility consumers from the manifest-freshness rule already owned by `decision-record.md`, then stage the global default one hub at a time while preserving `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:82:No runtime file, environment profile, manifest, CI job, hub directive, or frozen scorer file was changed while authoring this record.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:90:Delivery follows the ordered gates in `plan.md`: an operator go-ahead to begin, P0 safety surface, P1 drift enforcement, P2 canary, P3 derived eligibility, and P4 staged cutover. Each stage records parity, status, rollback, and scorer-integrity evidence before the next stage can begin. The implementation stops at the first failed gate.
